.TH "add_ino" 9 "add_ino" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
add_ino \- add an entry to the size tree.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" add_ino
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "ino_t inum "  ","
.BI "loff_t i_size "  ","
.BI "loff_t d_size "  ","
.BI "int exists "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "inum" 12
inode number
.IP "i_size" 12
size on inode
.IP "d_size" 12
maximum size based on data nodes
.IP "exists" 12
indicates whether the inode exists
